						               													<description>Blizword - for 1-4 players&amp;#10;A simple card game of wordforming.&amp;#10;components: 52 cards + 2 cards of rules&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Shuffle the cards and deal a 3x3 grid of letters face up between players. The remaining cards form the draw deck. In turn players remove letters from the grid that can form a complete word or the start of one. All letter tiles must be adjacent to one another in order: up, down, left, right or diagonally. 2, 3, 4 or more letters can be used.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;To score a word, square the number of letters (for instance):&amp;#10;S  T  O  R  A  = storage = 5 letters = 5x5 = 25 points&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Players should keep their letters in word stacks in front of them in separate piles for easy scoring.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The current player then replaces the removed cards in the grid with new cards from the draw deck. Play until the 3x3 grid cannot be completely re-filled from the draw deck. Highest score wins.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Variations&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Orientation Blizword: The orientation of the letters is important. You can only form a word and remove letters if the letters are in the same orientation. The letters H I N O S X and Z are the only valid in either orientation.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Solitaire Blizword: Beat your personal high score, removing sets of letters and replacing them as you go. Play until the 3x3 grid cannot be completely re-filled from the draw deck.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Advanced Blizword: You can only remove letters ONLY if they form the START of a word.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
